title: My phone cannot open some photos or videos. Why?
answer:
The phone does not support the file format. 

 The phone memory is insufficient. 

 The file has corrupted. 

 The file is copyright-protected (for example, a .dcf file). 

 The phone does not have sufficient resources. Close some third-party applications, and try again. 

 In some rare cases, unknown errors may occur in the phone's operating system or applications. Restart the phone and try again.
